1. **WORKFLOW 0 - Understand Project**: First, grasp the project structure — a pixel-perfect Raycast UI clone using React 19, Vite 6, Sass, TypeScript strict, Bun runtime.

2. **WORKFLOW 1 - Read progress.txt**: Identify the most important pending task. Tasks prefixed with `[P0]` are highest priority and must be done first. Tasks with `[P1000+]` are low-priority — do them when possible but don't block on them if higher-priority work exists.

3. **WORKFLOW 2 - No pending tasks**: If nothing is pending, plan improvements, add tasks, and stop.

4. **WORKFLOW 3 - Execute task**: Mark as IN_PROGRESS, evaluate scope (break if >3 files), execute, run `bun run check`, launch a review agent, consider improvements, implement corrections, update progress.txt, commit, output status block, stop.

